	<description>
            Le Chant du cygne is a french independent game collective formed by Gaël Bourhis, Simon Chauvin and Romain Enselme in 2015.
            Based in Paris and Lille, Le Chant du cygne develops experimental digital games. They created Palimpseste and are actively 
            working on Havre.
	</description>
		
	<histories>
		<history>
			<header>Origins</header>
			<text>
                            Le Chant du cygne was founded in 2015 by Romain, Gaël and Simon after two years working on solo projects and 
                            taking part in many game jams. They first started working together on a first person exploration game called 
                            Havre, which would become their most important project. In the mean time, they developed Palimpseste, an interactive
                            installation played with a custom headgear, that has been exhibited throughout Europe.
                        </text>
		</history>
	</histories>
		
